The information about the position of the ORFs within the longer sequence is currently contained in an IRanges object, let's convert it to a data frame so we can manipulate it more easily. We can do this with the `tibble` function.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
orf_df <- tibble(
  name = names(orfs),
  orf_start = start(orfs),
  orf_end = end(orfs),
  orf_width = width(orfs)
)
```
:::


::: {.callout-exercise #ex_blast_res_merge}
Merge this new data frame with information about your ORFs (`orf_df`) with the data frame with information about your BLAST results (`blast_expanded`) (as we did in @sec-merge). Name the resulting data frame variable `blast_combined`. View the result with `gt()`.

::: {.callout-answer #ex_blast_res_merfe_ans collapse="true"}


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
blast_combined <- full_join(blast_expanded, orf_df)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}

```
